On 3/27/03 9:20 PM, "Tom" <turtlebus(-at-)netzero.net> wrote:

> My 75 has a paint can lid type access lit in the engine compartment just
> ahead of the battery and just above the wheel well. Pops off with a
> screw driver. just enough access to change the filler neck if you have
> lots of patients and small arms and hands. Not sure if the 72 has the
> same arrangement.

Only the FI busses have the paint can lid. That area is open on older busses
and I think some models had the charcoal canister mounted there.

On 3/27/03 5:47 PM, "Edward Hilton" <ed.hilton(-at-)ptsem.edu> wrote:

> Also.  Fuel pump is weeping a drip of gas every so often.  Any sources for a
